      • a

        @Option
public double[] a
        An array containing values of the first parameter value.

      • a0

        @Option
public Double a0
        Alternate to "a". Builds a linear space of a coordinates. Use with "da" where "a0" is the starting coordinate and "da" the step.

        Default: 0

      • atype

        @Option
public CoordinateTypeEnum atype
        The coordinate type for the a data.

      • autocolorscale

        @Option
public Boolean autocolorscale
        Determines whether or not the colorscale is picked using the sign of the input z values.

      • autocontour

        @Option
public Boolean autocontour
        Determines whether or not the contour level attributes are picked by an algorithm. If "true" (the default), the number of contour levels can be set in "ncontours". If "false", set the contour level attributes in "contours".

      • b

        @Option
public double[][] b
        A two dimensional array of y coordinates at each carpet point.

      • b0

        @Option
public Double b0
        Alternate to "b". Builds a linear space of a coordinates. Use with "db" where "b0" is the starting coordinate and "db" the step.

        Default: 0

      • btype

        @Option
public CoordinateTypeEnum btype
        The coordinate type for the b data.

      • carpet

public String carpet
        The "carpet" of the carpet axes on which this contour trace lies.

      • colorbar

        @Option
public final ColorbarOptions colorbar
        Settings for the colorbar.

      • colorscale

        @Option
public Object[] colorscale
        The colorscale. Must be an array containing arrays mapping a normalized value to an rgb, rgba, hex, hsl, hsv, or named color string. At minimum, a mapping for the lowest (0) and highest (1) values are required. For example, "[[0, "rgb(0,0,255)", [1, "rgb(255,0,0)"]]". To control the bounds of the colorscale in z space, use zmin and zmax

      • contours

        @Option
public final ContoursOptions contours
        Controls how data are represented within a contour plot.

      • da

        @Option
public Double da
        The a coordinate step. See "a0" for more info.

        Default: 1

      • db

        @Option
public Double db
        The b coordinate step. See "b0" for more info.

        Default: 1

      • fillcolor

        @Option
public String fillcolor
        The fill color if "contours.type" is "constraint".

        Default: a half-transparent variant of the line color, marker color, or marker line color, whichever is available.

      • line_color

        @Option(value="line.color")
public String line_color
        The color of line bounding the box(es).

      • line_dash$enum

        The dash style of lines.

        Default: SOLID

        An alternative in the form of a dash length list in px (eg "5px,10px,2px,2px").

      • line_smoothing

        @Option(value="line.smoothing")
public Double line_smoothing
        Has an effect only if "shape" is set to "spline" The amount of smoothing. "0" corresponds to no smoothing (equivalent to a "linear" shape).

        Default: 1

      • line_width

        @Option(value="line.width")
public Integer line_width
        The width (in px) of line bounding the box(es).

      • ncontours

        @Option
public Integer ncontours
        The maximum number of contour levels. The actual number of contours will be chosen automatically to be less than or equal to the value of "ncontours". Has an effect only if "autocontour" is "true" or if "contours.size" is missing.

        Constraints: >0

        Default: 15

public String xaxis

      • yaxis
